What Exactly Is Orion?
Orion is an indexer and search engine for torrent, usenet, and hoster links. Orion provides an easy-to-use API which is integrated into a wide range of Kodi addons and mobile apps, allowing you to quickly find links for your favourite movies and TV shows.

Orion is not a debird service, it does not host or distribute any files. Instead, Orion complements debrid services. A streaming addon retrieves links from Orion and then passes it on to a debird service for download. You can also use Orion without a debrid service, by either using a torrent streaming addon like Elementum, using a standalone download manager, or accessing hoster links that can be played directly without a debrid service.

Orion is a community-maintained database with a number of advantages over using local scrapers from your streaming addon. Firstly, scraping is a lot faster, since only a single request has to be made instead of contacting many different websites. Secondly, you have access to links from sites that were taken down or are otherwise blocked by your country or ISP. Thirdly, you have access to links from a number of premium sites that require a separate paid subscription. And lastly, Orion keeps an extensive set of metadata, including the video and audio details, file hashes, and user popularity, which makes picking the best link a lot easier.

New Release

The new update is live! These are the main additions:

1. New Debrid Service: Orion now supports Debrider.app. There are still some minor issues with Debrider 's usenet and hoster integration, which will improve over the coming weeks. But the basics already work, including torrent cache lookups, cached streaming, adding new downloads, and auto-removal of finished torrent downloads.

2. Language Sorting: There is a new "sortlanguages" attribute in the API which allows sorting based on the audio and subtitle languages. Previously only filtering by language was possible, which removed streams from the results. By sorting instead of filtering, streams in your preferred language are now moved to the top of the results, without removing anything. Streams with audio in your preferred language are listed first, followed by streams with matching subtitles, followed by all other non-matching streams. You can specify multiple languages to sort by in order of preference, and you are also able to combine this with the other sort options. If you use a standalone app that has a link generator, you can add this to the "Additional Parameters". If you are using Kodi, you can specify language sorting in the Orion addon settings. Just note that most Kodi addons apply their own sorting and might therefore list the streams in a different order.

3. Database Optimization: Various database optimizations, cleanup and compression was applied. This should improve query speed slightly.

4. New Reseller: A new reseller, TakePremium, has been added with some alternative payment options.

5. New Addon: A new Kodi addon (v5.1.2) with all the new features has been released.

22 Sep 2025
System Update

A full system update is scheduled for Monday (8 September) which among other things will add support for a new debrid service. Since our database has grown so massive, it will take a little over a week to complete. During this time the server might occasionally be slow, but should remain operational and not cause interruptions to the API flow.

We apologies for any inconvenience. A new announcement will be posted once everything is ready.

3 Sep 2025
API Update

Today's API update comes with two new features.

Orion now tracks the debrid cache statuses for services that do not support cache lookups through their APIs anymore, namely RealDebrid, AllDebrid, and DebridLink. Every time a user successfully resolves a link through a debrid service on Orion, the cache status for that link is updated. It will probably take a few weeks or months until enough of these have trickled in, but over the long run this should create a decent cache lookup system for these restricted debrid services.

Searching with full-text queries is now a lot more accurate and faster. Most apps/addons search Orion using a Trakt, TMDb, TVDb, or IMDb ID, which is the preferred approach. However, apps that use full-text queries instead of IDs, now utilize an improved search algorithm, which is faster, substantially more accurate, and can better handle partial queries, queries with typos, and alias titles.

21 Jul 2025
Scraping Delay

There were some issues with the Trakt API over the past 48 hours, which prevented new links from being added. The issue has been resolved and scraping has resumed, but it might take some time until scraping has caught up with the new releases over the past days.
